(267, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 90, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"951\", \"958\", \"964\", \"997\", \"1021\", \"1070\", \"1071\", \"1072\", \"1073\", \"1074\", \"1075\", \"1076\", \"1077\"], \"title\": \"U1 L3: The Ottoman Empire\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"633\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation on the Ottoman Empire traces its rise under Osman I and Mehmed II with the conquest of Constantinople, and highlights Suleiman the Magnificent’s Golden Age of expansion, legal reforms, and cultural achievements by Mimar Sinan, poets, and artists.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: Ottoman Cultural Showcase, Tolerant City Map, Empire Mapping, and Millet System Role-Play.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of governance through Islamic values of justice and mercy, the Millet System and Shariah–Kanun balance, and awareness of the empire’s decline after World War I and enduring legacy in modern Istanbul and regional culture.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-08-31 22:31:36');
