(268, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 91, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"951\", \"958\", \"965\", \"988\", \"1060\", \"1078\", \"1079\", \"1080\", \"1081\"], \"title\": \"U2 L1: Migration Patterns and Cultural Diffusion\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"633\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces migration, its types (internal and international), and key causes such as jobs, safety, education, and religious freedom.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: Migration Suitcase, Push–Pull Sorting Game, Cultural Welcome Poster, and Role-Play on migrant life.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of push–pull factors, how migration leads to cultural diffusion through food, art, language, and traditions, and highlights Islamic perspectives on fairness, kindness, and hospitality with case studies of Gulf workers and the Prophet Muhammad’s (PBUH) migration to Madinah.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-08-31 22:31:54'),
(269, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 92, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"951\", \"958\", \"965\", \"1008\", \"1009\", \"1021\", \"1082\", \"1083\"], \"title\": \"U2 L2: Urbanization and the Growth of Cities\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"633\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation explains the causes of urban growth, such as jobs, services, education, and infrastructure, and highlights historical Islamic cities like Makkah, Madinah, Baghdad, and Cairo as centers of trade, religion, and learning.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: Design Your Ideal Saudi City, City Challenges Role Play, “Build Back Better” Poster, and City Soundscape Writing.</p></li><li><p>Promotes awareness of the challenges of urbanization—traffic, housing, pollution, and resource pressure—while showcasing Saudi initiatives like Green Riyadh, NEOM, and new metro systems for sustainable city planning.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-08-31 22:32:18'),
(270, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 93, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"951\", \"958\", \"966\", \"984\", \"1040\", \"1048\", \"1084\", \"1085\", \"1086\"], \"title\": \"U3 L1: Forms of Government\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"633\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces monarchy, democracy, republic, and theocracy with examples and key features, explaining the strengths and challenges of each system, such as stability, equality, representation, and faith-based governance.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Includes interactive activities: Government Role Cards role-play, Design Your Own Government, Saudi Arabia’s Fact Map, and Reflection Journal “If I Were a Leader…”.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of Saudi Arabia’s absolute monarchy rooted in Islam and tribal traditions, with the King as head of state and the Shura Council as an advisory body, while encouraging students to compare systems and reflect on leadership and values</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-08-31 22:32:45'),
(271, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 94, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"958\", \"966\", \"1012\", \"1087\", \"1088\", \"1089\", \"1090\", \"1091\", \"1092\", \"1093\", \"1094\", \"1095\"], \"title\": \"U3 L2: The Role of International Organizations\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"633\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation explains what international organizations are and how they address global issues such as peace, health, education, climate, and trade.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Includes interactive activities: Model UN Simulation, OIC Map Collaboration, Global Problem Solvers task, and Peace Through Cooperation poster.</p></li><li><p>Promotes awareness of the United Nations (UN), Organization of Islamic Cooperation (OIC), Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC), and other bodies such as the WHO, WTO, IMF, and the Arab League, while connecting to Islamic values of peace, fairness, and cooperation and highlighting Saudi Arabia’s active leadership role.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-08-31 22:33:00'),
(272, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 95, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"951\", \"958\", \"967\", \"1005\", \"1006\", \"1007\", \"1008\", \"1089\", \"1096\", \"1097\", \"1098\"], \"title\": \"U4 L1: Distribution of Natural Resources\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"633\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces different types of natural resources and explains the uneven global distribution caused by geology and climate.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: Resource Sorting Challenge, Mapping Saudi Arabia’s Resources, Debate on Ownership, and Reflection on Resource Fairness.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of oil, mineral, and water distribution worldwide, with a focus on Saudi Arabia’s oil, gas, minerals, and freshwater challenges, while highlighting global alliances such as OPEC, GCC, UNEP, and OIC, and connecting to Islamic values of avoiding waste (Israf) and stewardship (Khilafah) within Saudi Vision 2030’s sustainability goals.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-08-31 22:33:23'),
(273, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 96, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"951\", \"958\", \"967\", \"1005\", \"1006\", \"1007\", \"1008\", \"1009\", \"1013\", \"1099\", \"1100\"], \"title\": \"U4 L2: Saudi Arabia’s Role in the Global Economy\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"633\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation explains how the 1938 discovery of oil in Dhahran transformed Saudi Arabia into a global economic power, highlighting economic growth through industrial cities like Jubail and Yanbu, modern infrastructure, and expanded education and healthcare.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Includes interactive activities: Timeline Challenge, Stewardship Debate, Vision 2030 Role Cards, and Design a Green City.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of Saudi Arabia’s influence through OPEC, global partnerships, and events like the 1973 oil crisis, while connecting stewardship and sustainability with Vision 2030’s goals for a vibrant society, thriving economy, and ambitious nation, and featuring major projects such as NEOM, the Red Sea Project, and the Saudi Green Initiative.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-08-31 22:33:48'),
(274, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 97, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"958\", \"988\", \"995\", \"1041\", \"1101\", \"1102\"], \"title\": \"U5 L1: Cultural Interactions and Influences\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"633\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation defines cultural exchange through trade, migration, travel, and technology, emphasizing its role in building connections and innovation.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: Golden Age Role Cards, Culture Web, Globalization Debate, and Preserving My Culture Action Plan.</p></li><li><p>Promotes appreciation of the Islamic Golden Age, awareness of globalization’s benefits and challenges, and the importance of balancing global connections with cultural preservation.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-08-31 22:34:03'),
(275, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 98, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"958\", \"985\", \"1012\", \"1101\", \"1103\", \"1104\", \"1105\", \"1106\", \"1107\"], \"title\": \"U5 L2: Leadership and Responsibility in a Global Context\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"633\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces leadership at community, national, and global levels, with examples from disaster relief, reform, and advocacy.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: Leadership Ladder growth plan, Youth Leadership Campaign, Leadership Code of Ethics, and Role Cards – Meet the Leaders.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of leadership qualities, Islamic principles of accountability and service, and the value of responsible action in a global context.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-08-31 22:34:18'),
(276, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 99, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"951\", \"959\", \"964\", \"1021\", \"1070\", \"1108\", \"1109\", \"1110\", \"1111\", \"1112\", \"1113\", \"1114\"], \"title\": \"U1 L1: World War I and the Changing World Order\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"634\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces World War I (1914–1918), its global scale, alliances, and impact on millions, explaining the MAIN causes: Militarism, Alliances, Imperialism, and Nationalism.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Includes interactive activities: World Map Challenge, Alliance Sorting, Timeline Challenge, and Think About It discussion.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of the Allies and Central Powers, Saudi regions under Ottoman influence, life during the war, and the lasting effects of the Treaty of Versailles and the Ottoman Empire’s fall.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-09-01 00:23:33'),
(277, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 100, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"951\", \"959\", \"964\", \"1021\", \"1114\", \"1115\", \"1116\", \"1117\", \"1118\", \"1119\"], \"title\": \"U1 L2: The Interwar Period and National Movements\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"634\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation explores the interwar years marked by economic, political, and social challenges, including the Great Depression, and shows how the collapse of empires and redrawn borders fueled nationalism and independence movements in Asia and Africa.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: Timeline Puzzle, Voices of Freedom reflection, and National Movement Poster design.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of Atatürk’s reforms in Turkey, the protests in Egypt, Gandhi’s peaceful resistance in India, Saudi Arabia’s unification under King Abdulaziz in 1932, and the discovery of oil in 1938 as a turning point.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-09-01 00:23:59'),
(278, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 101, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"951\", \"959\", \"964\", \"1021\", \"1120\", \"1121\", \"1122\", \"1123\", \"1124\", \"1125\"], \"title\": \"U1 L3: World War II and Global Realignment\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"634\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation covers World War II (1939–1945), the deadliest conflict in history with over 60 million lives lost, explaining causes such as the Treaty of Versailles, global depression, rise of dictators, militarism, and expansion by Germany, Italy, and Japan.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: Imagine the World in 1939, Cause-and-Effect Sort, Allies/Axis country naming, and Oil Matters discussion.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of the Allies and Axis powers, Saudi Arabia’s neutral stance yet vital oil support, and the war’s outcomes including the United Nations, independence movements, and the Cold War’s beginnings.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-09-01 00:26:00'),
(279, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 102, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"951\", \"959\", \"965\", \"1021\", \"1033\", \"1119\", \"1126\", \"1127\", \"1128\", \"1129\", \"1130\", \"1131\"], \"title\": \"U2 L1: Decolonization in the Middle East and Africa\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"634\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation explains decolonization as nations in the Middle East and Africa gained independence after World War II, highlighting causes such as weakened European powers, rising demand for self-rule, and global pressure for equality and human rights.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: Freedom Metaphor Map, Timeline Challenge, and Build a Nation Roleplay.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of key independence movements in Egypt, Sudan, Ghana, and Algeria, the challenges of nation-building, and Saudi Arabia’s support for Arab nations.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-09-01 00:26:12'),
(280, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 103, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"951\", \"959\", \"965\", \"1021\", \"1132\", \"1134\", \"1135\", \"1136\", \"1137\", \"1138\", \"1139\", \"1140\", \"1141\", \"1142\", \"1143\", \"1144\"], \"title\": \"U2 L2: The Cold War and Regional Conflicts\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"634\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces the Cold War rivalry between the USA and USSR after World War II, defined by ideological conflict without direct fighting, and explains its causes, such as capitalism vs. communism, democracy vs. one-party rule, fear, and mistrust.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Includes interactive activities: Cold War Timeline, True or False on proxy wars, and Alliance Sorting Game.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of major Cold War events, proxy wars and alliances, and the conflict’s global impact ending with the Soviet Union’s collapse in 1991.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-09-01 00:26:36'),
(281, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 104, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"951\", \"959\", \"966\", \"1008\", \"1011\", \"1021\", \"1058\", \"1145\", \"1146\", \"1147\", \"1148\", \"1149\"], \"title\": \"U3 L1: Understanding Climate Change\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"634\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces climate as long-term weather patterns and explains how human activity drives rapid climate change, with causes such as burning fossil fuels, deforestation, factories, and vehicles.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: True or False quiz, Spot the Cause, What Would You Do? reflection, and Green Pledge.</p></li><li><p>Promotes awareness of climate change signs, its impact on Saudi Arabia, and the importance of sustainable solutions like conservation, tree planting, and solar energy.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-09-01 00:26:49'),
(282, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 105, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"951\", \"959\", \"966\", \"1007\", \"1008\", \"1009\", \"1011\", \"1150\"], \"title\": \"U3 L2: Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs)\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"634\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces the UN’s 17 Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) to address global challenges like poverty, pollution, and inequality, and explains why they were created to ensure a fairer, healthier, and sustainable future for all.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Includes interactive activity: <em>My City, My Goal</em> reflection linking local actions to SDGs.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of the three pillars of sustainable development—economy, society, and environment—and connects the SDGs to Saudi Vision 2030 projects such as NEOM that promote clean energy, jobs, education, and health.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-09-01 00:27:10'),
(283, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 106, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"951\", \"959\", \"967\", \"997\", \"1040\", \"1085\", \"1151\", \"1152\"], \"title\": \"U4 L1: Comparative Governance Systems\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"634\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces the purpose of governments and how they affect daily life through services like schools, healthcare, and safety, while explaining the main forms of governance, such as monarchy, democracy, and authoritarianism, with global examples.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Government in My Life</em> reflection and <em>What If You Were a Leader?</em> discussion.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of Saudi Arabia’s monarchy based on the Qur’an and Sunnah, supported by the Council of Ministers and Shura Council, and encourages reflection on leadership and values.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-09-01 00:27:45'),
(284, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 108, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"951\", \"959\", \"967\", \"1007\", \"1009\", \"1099\", \"1150\", \"1153\"], \"title\": \"U4 L2: Saudi Arabia’s Vision 2030\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"634\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces Vision 2030, Saudi Arabia’s national plan built on the three pillars of a Vibrant Society, Thriving Economy, and Ambitious Nation.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Build Your NEOM</em> design, <em>Eco-Tourism Slogan</em>, and <em>My Future Role</em> reflection.</p></li><li><p>Promotes awareness of major projects like NEOM, Qiddiya, and the Red Sea Project, while emphasizing opportunities for Saudi youth in education, technology, tourism, and entrepreneurship.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-09-01 00:28:11'),
(285, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 109, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"959\", \"1005\", \"1089\", \"1092\", \"1101\", \"1154\", \"1155\", \"1156\"], \"title\": \"U5 L1: International Trade and Organizations\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"634\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation explains why countries trade—since no nation produces everything it needs, imports and exports connect economies—and defines international trade with its benefits, such as wider products, economic growth, jobs, and stronger global ties.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Trade Match</em> game, <em>Who’s Who in Trade</em> matching, and Quick Quiz.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of Saudi Arabia’s trade role (exports in oil, plastics, chemicals; imports in machinery, vehicles, electronics) and awareness of key trade organizations like the WTO, GCC, and OPEC.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-09-01 00:28:37'),
(286, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 111, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"959\", \"968\", \"1007\", \"1009\", \"1015\", \"1101\", \"1157\", \"1158\"], \"title\": \"U5 L2: Technology and Economic Development\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"634\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation explores how technology shapes modern life, from cities and schools to healthcare and businesses, and connects to Saudi Arabia’s Vision 2030 with NEOM as a model smart city powered by robotics, clean energy, and innovation.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>My Smart City</em> design, <em>Tech-at-Home</em> reflection, and <em>Technology Debate</em>.</p></li><li><p>Promotes awareness of technology’s impact across sectors like education, healthcare, business, and agriculture, while encouraging reflection on its benefits and drawbacks in daily life.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-09-01 00:29:24'),
(287, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 112, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"959\", \"1007\", \"1009\", \"1013\", \"1159\", \"1160\", \"1161\", \"1162\", \"1163\"], \"title\": \"U6 L1: Environmental Stewardship and Responsibility\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"634\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation defines stewardship (Amanah) and the Islamic view of humans as Khalifa (caretakers) of Earth, while explaining ecosystems and biodiversity and the threats posed by pollution, deforestation, overfishing, and climate change.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Ecosystem Chain Game</em>, <em>Green Saudi Action Board</em>, <em>Model Ecosystem</em> terrarium, and <em>Qur’an &amp; Nature</em> Poster.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of Islamic teachings on nature, Saudi initiatives like Vision 2030 and the Green Saudi Initiative, and global agreements such as the Paris Agreement and Kyoto Protocol.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-09-01 00:29:49'),
(288, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 113, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"959\", \"1010\", \"1011\", \"1103\", \"1159\", \"1164\", \"1165\", \"1166\"], \"title\": \"U6 L2: The Role of Global Citizenship\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"634\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation defines global citizenship as awareness that personal choices affect others and the planet, paired with responsibility and fairness, and highlights key traits such as empathy, respect for diversity, collaboration, responsibility, and advocacy.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Global Citizenship Trait March</em>, <em>Voices of Change</em> posters, <em>Local-to-Global Impact Mapping</em>, <em>Citizenship in Islam</em> collage, and <em>Global Problem-Solving Circle</em>.</p></li><li><p>Promotes reflection on real-world change makers, the importance of cooperation on issues like climate change, poverty, and inequality, and the role of Islamic values in guiding global responsibility.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-09-01 00:30:05'),
(289, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 114, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"960\", \"964\", \"968\", \"1100\", \"1167\", \"1168\", \"1169\", \"1170\", \"1171\"], \"title\": \"U1 L1: Introduction to Physical Geography\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"635\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces physical geography and its importance in understanding Earth’s natural features and hazards, covering Earth’s layers, tectonic plates, mountains, rivers, deserts, and oceans.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Disaster-Ready City</em> design and <em>Quick Check</em> review.</p></li><li><p>Promotes awareness of natural processes like weathering, erosion, and landscape change, human impact on the environment, and stewardship linked to Islamic values.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-09-01 02:40:24'),
(290, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 115, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"960\", \"964\", \"974\", \"1171\", \"1172\", \"1173\", \"1174\"], \"title\": \"U1 L2: Weather and Climate Basics\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"635\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation explains the difference between weather (short-term conditions) and climate (long-term patterns), introducing key elements such as temperature, precipitation, wind, and humidity.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Create a Climate Map</em>, <em>Weather Prediction Simulation</em>, and class presentations on regional climates.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of factors shaping climate zones, awareness of global climate patterns, and Islamic reflections on natural phenomena as signs of Allah’s creation.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-09-01 02:40:38'),
(291, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 116, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"960\", \"964\", \"968\", \"974\", \"1175\", \"1176\", \"1177\", \"1178\"], \"title\": \"U1 L3: Earth’s Water Systems\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"635\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces the hydrological cycle, the difference between saltwater and freshwater, and Earth’s major water bodies, highlighting the role of processes like transpiration for Saudi ecosystems.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Interpreting Water Data</em>, <em>Design a Water-Smart City</em>, and <em>Test Your Knowledge</em>.</p></li><li><p>Promotes awareness of water challenges in Saudi Arabia, global scarcity concerns, sustainable solutions, and Islamic teachings on water as a sacred trust.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-09-01 02:40:49'),
(292, 1, 'RESOURCE_UPDATED', 117, '{\"updatedFields\": {\"tags\": [\"960\", \"964\", \"1011\", \"1161\", \"1179\", \"1180\"], \"title\": \"U1 L4: Ecosystems and Biodiversity\", \"status\": \"draft\", \"type_id\": \"366\", \"grade_id\": \"635\", \"subject_id\": \"436\", \"description\": \"<ul><li><p>This presentation defines ecosystems and explains the interaction of biotic (living) and abiotic (non-living) factors, while emphasizing the importance of biodiversity and the risks posed when key species are lost.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Eco-Role-play</em> (students act as ecologists) and <em>Ecosystems Check-In</em> review.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of threats such as habitat destruction, pollution, and climate change, the importance of conservation strategies, and Islamic values of stewardship and care for Allah’s creation.</p></li></ul><p></p>\"}}', '127.0.0.1', NULL, '2025-09-01 02:41:04'),
