(146, 'U3 L5: Islamic Civilization’s Global Impact', '<ul><li><p>This presentation examines the global influence of Islamic civilization through trade networks, cultural exchange, education, governance, and social welfare.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Matching Contributions</em> to modern equivalents and a <em>Legacy Map</em> presentation to trace Islamic influence worldwide.</p></li><li><p>Promotes appreciation of Islamic principles of tolerance, justice, and charity, along with the enduring legacy of scientific, cultural, and social contributions.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 636, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756733164353-cc0849d8-91fb-4f3a-98e8-1c5effe5bfe6.pptx', 'SS_Hist1_G10_U3_L5.pptx', 3075944, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756733164371-6db350c6-3cbb-43ea-80b0-5a6ca27856ea.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 06:26:04', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 39),
(147, 'U4 L1: The Persian Empire', '<ul><li><p>This presentation explores the rise of the Persian Empire, its governance through the satrapy system, and the cultural influence seen in Persian architecture, art, literature, and philosophy.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Source Analysis</em> of the Cyrus Cylinder and <em>Build Your Own Empire</em> role-play.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of values such as justice, fairness, and cultural tolerance in Persian rule and their echoes in modern governance.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 636, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756733256393-dee83b87-7996-4bfc-8199-af081914d011.pptx', 'SS_Hist1_G10_U4_L1.pptx', 4267186, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756733256414-4abf7927-cae0-4113-9588-40f8ab2cb31d.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 06:27:36', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 38),
(148, 'U4 L2: The Greek Empire – Foundations of Western Civilization', '<ul><li><p>This presentation examines the geography of Greek city-states, the contrasts between Athens and Sparta, and key historical events such as the Persian Wars, Peloponnesian War, and the rise of Alexander the Great.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Athens vs. Sparta Debate</em> and <em>Match the Contribution</em> to explore Greek cultural and political achievements.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of the Golden Age of Athens, the foundations of democracy, and Greece’s lasting influence on world history.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 636, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756733416912-d19d0385-b68b-455e-b25e-c7e95d640f30.pptx', 'SS_Hist1_G10_U4_L2.pptx', 9390702, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756733417181-5d39e02e-25ba-4205-b1b8-c02162d77585.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 06:30:17', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 37),
(149, 'U4 L3: The Roman Empire', '<ul><li><p>This presentation explores the rise and expansion of Rome, covering the Punic Wars, the leadership of Julius Caesar and Augustus, and the Pax Romana.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Engineering Matching</em> to connect Roman innovations with their purposes, and discussion tasks on leadership, stability, and administration.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of Rome’s legal and administrative systems, engineering achievements, and the empire’s lasting influence on governance, infrastructure, and culture.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 636, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756733507428-d6f05ef4-dc07-4151-8d13-30872d940fe6.pptx', 'SS_Hist1_G10_U4_L3.pptx', 4165483, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756733507449-e22cb046-12dc-4c35-8e9b-1190c29f5122.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 06:31:47', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 36),
(150, 'U4 L4: The Ottoman Empire', '<ul><li><p>This presentation examines the origins, expansion, and governance of the Ottoman Empire, highlighting the leadership of Suleiman the Magnificent and contributions in science, architecture, art, poetry, and literature.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activity: <em>Timeline Sort</em> of key events to understand the empire’s growth, decline, and dissolution.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of the Ottoman legacy, reasons for its fall, the role of Mustafa Kemal Atatürk, and the unification of Saudi Arabia under King Abdulaziz as a revival of identity and values.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 636, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756733710233-eaf44121-94b5-4ec3-bc3e-23294e2594b8.pptx', 'SS_Hist1_G10_U4_L4.pptx', 39205236, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756733714569-a8ac1365-ece0-43ca-a377-92713aa6c64a.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 06:35:14', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 35),
(151, 'U4 L5: Cultural and Religious Exchanges', '<ul><li><p>This presentation explores the Middle East as a crossroads of cultures, highlighting Baghdad’s role in global learning and the influence of trade routes beyond economics.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activity: <em>Cultural Influence Match-Up</em> to connect exchanges in science, mathematics, food, and faith traditions across civilizations.</p></li><li><p>Promotes appreciation of intellectual and cultural exchange during the Islamic Golden Age, the spread of values through religion, and Islamic teachings on learning from others.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 636, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756733881692-501446ad-584f-4f75-b4b5-47337eef218b.pptx', 'SS_Hist1_G10_U4_L5.pptx', 8782273, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756733881883-c9952ac7-bc1b-43f9-a194-b91e0adc6106.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 06:38:01', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 34),
(152, 'U4 L6: The Impact of Empire on Modern Borders and Conflicts', '<ul><li><p>This presentation examines how empires shaped modern borders, the tensions they created, and case studies such as the Kurds.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Border Tracing</em> and <em>Conflict Role-play,</em> where students analyze empire-border conflicts and propose peaceful solutions.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of empire legacies, Islamic values in conflict resolution, and the importance of justice and peaceful coexistence.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 636, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756734036021-291f122b-07a4-46d9-add2-b695ca327967.pptx', 'SS_Hist1_G10_U4_L6.pptx', 9556181, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756734036312-6aae3cd3-a4d6-499f-89ff-97dc79931179.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 06:40:36', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 33),
(153, 'U1 L1: Introduction to Demography (Part1 )', '<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces demography, its core concepts, and the factors influencing population changes, using Saudi Arabia’s recent population growth as a case study.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive discussions on population distribution, birth rates, death rates, migration, and aging, with questions linking to Saudi society and economy.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of demographic dynamics, their social, economic, and policy implications, and the role of culture, religion, and healthcare in shaping population trends.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 637, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756734174212-909abdd1-cab1-46bc-a3b5-acb1c71ab6e3.pptx', 'SS_Geo2_G11_U1_L1_Part1.pptx', 826274, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756734174214-828204bc-1945-45aa-8531-0c1bb6501a9d.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 06:42:54', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 32),
(154, 'U1 L1: Introduction to Demography (Part 2)', '<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces demography and its key concepts - population size, distribution, birth rates, death rates, migration, aging, and life expectancy—using Saudi Arabia and global comparisons.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: discussions on population trends, <em>Socratic Q&amp;A</em> on birth and death rates, <em>Team Investigation</em> of life expectancy in Japan, Nigeria, and Saudi Arabia, and case-based tasks on aging populations.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of demographic dynamics, their social, economic, and policy implications, and connects Saudi Arabia’s Vision 2030 strategies to managing aging populations and healthcare needs.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 637, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756734253571-11b9385c-7a48-4f81-a3f0-cd98d018da60.pptx', 'SS_Geo2_G11_U1_L1_Part2.pptx', 2082186, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756734253577-67b26dfd-6d02-4d77-8c3f-b42d18658e6c.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 06:44:13', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 31),
(156, 'U1 L2: Factors Influencing Population Growth', '<ul><li><p>This presentation explains the economic, social, cultural, environmental, and political factors that influence population growth, with examples from Saudi Arabia and global case studies.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Role Play</em> on the impact of economic recession, <em>Family Choices Across Cultures</em> research (Nigeria, Japan, India, Germany), and <em>Design a Population Policy</em> group task linked to Vision 2030.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of how economic conditions, migration, cultural norms, and environmental changes shape population growth and distribution, while encouraging policy-based solutions.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 637, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756734474874-a4e31c35-63e9-4f69-8c1f-f66c6f0c8599.pptx', 'SS_Geo2_G11_U1_L2.pptx', 1702185, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756734474882-2b158f17-5a6f-4ae6-a0db-a05d0bba47c9.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 06:47:54', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 30),
(157, 'U1 L3: Migration Patterns and Their Impacts', '<ul><li><p>This presentation defines migration, its types, and the push–pull factors that influence movement, using global and Saudi examples.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Migration Decision Simulation</em> with role-play scenarios and <em>Ripple Effect Analysis</em> to study economic, social, and environmental impacts.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of how migration shapes societies, economies, and environments, while linking to Saudi Arabia’s Vision 2030 strategies for sustainable urban growth</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 637, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756734830116-9fc20195-c75c-47ce-b9a2-ff93c5af1a05.pptx', 'SS_Geo2_G11_U1_L3.pptx', 541902, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756734830119-71635a06-e7e9-4c69-8f0e-acb4ef206578.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 06:53:50', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 29),
(158, 'U1 L4: Population Policies and Their Implications', '<ul><li><p>This presentation examines population policies, including pro-natalist and anti-natalist strategies, and how migration policies influence demographic balance.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activity: <em>Vision 2030 Impact Map,</em> where students link initiatives like NEOM, Green Riyadh, Saudization, and tourism projects to population outcomes.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of how policies shape population growth, the challenges of extreme growth rates, and Saudi Arabia’s Vision 2030 goals for sustainable demographic management.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 637, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756735174093-f70a80ba-6876-456b-b0d7-4a24bcf88c24.pptx', 'SS_Geo2_G11_U1_L4.pptx', 1356188, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756735174098-f96a1a95-bdb7-4aee-877f-67708c1b6982.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 06:59:34', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 28),
(159, 'U2 L1: Understanding Urbanization', '<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces the concept of urbanization, its historical trends, and the economic, social, technological, and policy factors driving population shifts from rural to urban areas.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activity: <em>Design Your Future City,</em> where students create sustainable city models addressing growth, sustainability, and inclusivity.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of the social, economic, and environmental impacts of urbanization globally and in Saudi Arabia, while encouraging solutions for future challenges.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 637, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756735331537-69f6cb9f-a1d2-4279-949c-68740ce5d9b7.pptx', 'SS_Geo2_G11_U2_L1.pptx', 3650269, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756735331550-960d9129-206c-42d0-acc7-dd2b1fc2759d.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 07:02:11', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 27),
(160, 'U2 L2: Social and Economic Impacts of Urbanization', '<ul><li><p>This presentation examines the positive and negative effects of urbanization, including improved education, healthcare, and cultural diversity, alongside challenges such as overcrowding, inequality, and weakened community bonds.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Case Study Comparison</em> (Copenhagen, Tokyo, Lagos) and an <em>Interactive Reflection Circle</em> on local urbanization impacts and solutions.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of how urbanization shapes societies and economies, and encourages students to evaluate strategies relevant to Saudi Arabia.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 637, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756735422077-8d39cfe2-fd10-4b4c-a05a-72cbc2f44de8.pptx', 'SS_Geo2_G11_U2_L2.pptx', 2118701, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756735422084-7d039ebb-4fe9-47cf-844f-959141b587e8.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 07:03:42', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 26),
(161, 'U2 L3: Environmental Consequences of Urbanization', '<ul><li><p>This presentation explores the environmental impacts of urbanization, including air and water pollution, soil degradation, waste challenges, loss of green spaces, and the urban heat island effect.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Urbanization Web Map</em>, <em>Quick Poll</em> on perceptions of urbanization, and <em>Brain Booster</em> tasks linking societal and environmental impacts to solutions.</p></li><li><p>Promotes awareness of sustainable urban development, the benefits of green spaces, and Vision 2030 initiatives addressing urban environmental challenges in Saudi Arabia.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 637, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756735523580-b1d03ac4-7374-40e1-90fb-ed6b45351e47.pptx', 'SS_Geo2_G11_U2_L3.pptx', 967773, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756735523584-0c225e92-c664-4d3d-bb18-6a83e15b95bf.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 07:05:23', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 25),
(162, 'U2 L4: Planning for Sustainable Urban Growth', '<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces the principles of sustainable urban planning, emphasizing efficient land use, integrated transportation, green infrastructure, and community involvement.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Collaborative Urban Planning Workshop,</em> where students role-play stakeholders to design sustainable projects, and case study discussions on Dubai, Curitiba, and NEOM.</p></li><li><p>Promotes awareness of balancing urban growth with sustainability, Vision 2030’s smart city initiatives, and lessons from global models.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 637, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756735666816-cde352b9-991d-4019-bef1-ccd08114a3df.pptx', 'SS_Geo2_G11_U2_L4.pptx', 4327860, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756735666854-7dec0e1d-7762-4e22-98ea-bb59825cf0fa.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 07:07:46', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 24),
(163, 'U3 L1: Introduction to Economic Geography', '<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces economic geography, its key concepts, and the factors influencing economic activities such as natural resources, climate, topography, and market access.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Map Analysis</em> of global resource distribution, sector exploration, and discussions on Vision 2030 initiatives like NEOM and tourism projects.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of the relationship between geography and economics, the uneven distribution of industries worldwide, and Saudi Arabia’s efforts at diversification and sustainability.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 637, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756735757583-7ce3c7e1-876b-4b37-91ff-cae2dddb7a28.pptx', 'SS_Geo2_G11_U3_L1.pptx', 6146459, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756735757632-26c94db4-863c-444c-a539-0050ca35f6e0.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 07:09:17', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 23),
(164, 'U3 L2: Global Trade and Interdependence', '<ul><li><p>This presentation defines global trade and economic interdependence, explaining exports, imports, and trade balance while highlighting the benefits and challenges of international exchange.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activity: <em>Global Trade Simulation,</em> where students act as exporters, mediators, and importers to negotiate trade deals.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of globalization, Saudi Arabia’s role in oil exports and imports of technology, and the importance of cooperation in sustaining global economies.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 637, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756735833099-5cda3848-961e-4003-9482-e088fc28d61d.pptx', 'SS_Geo2_G11_U3_L2.pptx', 2522774, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756735833120-c02d717e-e820-40fc-9885-8f0f9670394b.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 07:10:33', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 22),
(165, 'U3 L3: The Economics of Natural Resources', '<ul><li><p>This presentation explains renewable and non-renewable resources, their uneven distribution, and their economic and environmental impacts, with a focus on Saudi Arabia’s oil reserves and Vision 2030 sustainability goals.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Brainstorming Critical Resources</em>, <em>Socratic Discussion</em> on oil depletion, and <em>Group Task</em> to design a sustainable energy plan for Saudi Arabia.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of resource exploitation, job creation, environmental challenges, and strategies for sustainable management.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 637, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756735918903-ca56bee0-adce-4fef-9c75-ec5bcdc5561c.pptx', 'SS_Geo2_G11_U3_L3.pptx', 3020585, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756735918920-9997ffba-c33d-41cf-8c32-fcdd022e475f.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 07:11:58', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 21),
(166, 'U3 L4: Sustainable Economic Development', '<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces sustainable economic development, highlighting frameworks like the Triple Bottom Line (Profit, People, Planet) and the Circular Economy.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Socratic Discussion</em> on the Red Sea Project, case study analysis of Vision 2030 initiatives (NEOM, renewable energy, sustainable tourism), and a <em>Sustainability Proposal</em> group project.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of challenges in balancing profit, environment, and social equity while encouraging strategies for renewable energy, sustainable agriculture, cultural preservation, and inclusive growth.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 637, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756735984169-7824a971-9792-4a11-83fd-c7715c145d18.pptx', 'SS_Geo2_G11_U3_L4.pptx', 5215206, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756735984191-39b2e6fc-b375-4e0c-947b-ee375c5e3bf0.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 07:13:04', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 20),
(167, 'U4 L1: Introduction to Political and Cultural Geography', '<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces political and cultural geography, focusing on boundaries, sovereignty, geopolitics, cultural identity, and cultural diffusion.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Case Study</em> on Belgium’s linguistic divisions and <em>Cultural Diffusion in Action</em> group presentations (expansion, relocation, hierarchical diffusion).</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of how geography shapes political systems, cultural identity, and societal interactions, with connections to Saudi Arabia’s boundaries and cultural diffusion.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 637, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756736058269-d70717db-b508-4ed4-891e-19c757543a44.pptx', 'SS_Geo2_G11_U4_L1.pptx', 5673806, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756736058300-703f99ea-b244-4310-ba32-39199fb19150.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 07:14:18', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 19),
(168, 'U4 L2: The Role of Political Boundaries in Cultural Identity', '<ul><li><p>This presentation examines the historical significance of political boundaries, their impact on cultural identity, and case studies of border conflicts and cultural blending.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Personal Stories</em> on border influence, <em>Case Study</em> of the Kurdish population, and <em>Group Analysis</em> of UAE–Oman border cultural exchanges.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of nation-states, colonial boundaries, and how borders can unite or divide communities, with emphasis on regional history and identity.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 637, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756736117239-bb1851bf-7966-464e-8b47-d29b7d54e376.pptx', 'SS_Geo2_G11_U4_L2.pptx', 5157930, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756736117260-793a2d3c-e5cd-4b70-94de-dd77de97e34a.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 07:15:17', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 18),
(169, 'U4 L3: Cultural Changes in a Globalized World', '<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces globalization and cultural diffusion, analyzing their effects on cultural identity with a focus on Saudi Arabia’s experiences.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Inquiry Discussion</em> on cultural diffusion, <em>Socratic Reflection</em> on youth strategies, and a <em>Reflective Activity</em> linking globalization and Saudi culture.</p></li><li><p>Promotes awareness of globalization’s opportunities and challenges, strategies for cultural preservation, and Vision 2030 initiatives such as Diriyah restoration and cultural tourism.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 637, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756736246895-609e95cd-3e25-459b-9d2b-12dc52e3c293.pptx', 'SS_Geo2_G11_U4_L3.pptx', 4130564, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756736246910-cbede33c-3505-4ffe-b813-8faae88b6bcb.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 07:16:33', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 17),
(170, 'U4 L4: Political Decisions and Cultural Landscapes', '<ul><li><p>This presentation explores cultural landscapes as products of human activity, examining how political decisions influence urban planning, zoning, and heritage preservation.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Case Study</em> of Hammarby Sjöstad in Stockholm, analysis of Vision 2030 initiatives, and a <em>Creative Project</em> to design cultural preservation plans for local or regional sites.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of the role of governance in shaping cultural identity, the balance between development and heritage, and the global importance of preservation efforts.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 637, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756736308717-c03fd53e-5ee9-4d80-8ca3-47ff52b932ac.pptx', 'SS_Geo2_G11_U4_L4.pptx', 3149028, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756736308727-2068a626-bf26-489a-b2af-c0a10bd3a308.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 07:18:28', '2025-09-02 01:41:13', 16),
(171, 'U1 L1: The Renaissance – Rebirth of Arts and Sciences', '<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces the Renaissance as a period of rebirth in art, science, and literature, exploring its causes, humanism, and contributions to the modern world.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Renaissance Fact Sort</em> and <em>Then &amp; Now</em> comparison to link historical and modern advancements.</p></li><li><p>Promotes appreciation of Renaissance art, science, and literature, recognition of Islamic contributions through translation and knowledge transfer, and reflection on how seeking knowledge aligns with Islamic values.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 638, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756736526151-e90029eb-5706-43bb-a2fa-bdd5a85a9987.pptx', 'SS_Hist2_G12_U1_L1.pptx', 37858006, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756790602567-7dcb414d-81be-4701-b45e-427ea76bbd4e.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 07:22:10', '2025-09-02 02:20:23', 16),
(172, 'U1 L2: The Reformation – A Religious Transformation', '<ul><li><p>This presentation examines the causes and effects of the Reformation, focusing on Martin Luther’s 95 Theses, other reformers, and the Catholic Counter-Reformation.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Reform Comparison Chart</em> and <em>Debate Arena,</em> where students argue whether the Reformation was about belief or politics.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of how questioning authority sparked religious and political change, the role of technology in spreading ideas, and the lasting impact of reform movements on society.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 638, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756791123623-6463fd6f-481f-441f-9045-9e9106b9642d.pptx', 'SS_Hist2_G12_U1_L2.pptx', 63091704, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756791131212-0f8c2024-95fb-44a4-99a3-7518ae13a0a3.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 22:32:11', '2025-09-02 02:20:23', 15),
(173, 'U1 L3: The Enlightenment – The Rise of Reason', '<ul><li><p>This presentation explores Enlightenment ideals such as reason, free will, and challenges to tradition, highlighting their influence on revolutions and modern thought.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Enlightenment Matching</em> and <em>Enlightenment Role-play,</em> where students embody thinkers to debate key ideas.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of the relevance of Enlightenment principles today, their connections to Islamic values, and how ideas can drive social and political change.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 638, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756792433081-3f5339fa-da7c-4c7a-8953-f28df692b84c.pptx', 'SS_Hist2_G12_U1_L3.pptx', 8234697, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756792433195-c2f4e5c6-535d-4cf9-bcbe-03e7d6297f53.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 22:53:53', '2025-09-02 02:20:23', 14),
(174, 'U1 L4: The Scientific Revolution – A New View of the Universe', '<ul><li><p>This presentation examines the causes and key discoveries of the Scientific Revolution, emphasizing contributions from Muslim scholars and global influences on European science.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Scientist Timeline</em> and <em>Debate the Discovery,</em> where students defend traditional vs. new scientific perspectives.</p></li><li><p>Promotes appreciation of scientific inquiry, the relationship between reason and faith, and the importance of acknowledging diverse contributions to global knowledge.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 638, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756792571340-e5c3131c-75e6-44f3-a538-94eb136962cc.pptx', 'SS_Hist2_G12_U1_L4.pptx', 4300660, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756792571356-7897b28f-72f7-4193-953d-5df41e234979.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 22:56:11', '2025-09-02 02:20:23', 13),
(175, 'U2 L1: The Industrial Revolution – A Technological Transformation', '<ul><li><p>This presentation explores the Agricultural Revolution as a foundation, the key inventions and inventors of the Industrial Revolution, and the conditions in Britain that made industrialization possible.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Factory Simulation</em> role-play to model production lines and <em>Learning Chronicle Reflection</em> on the impact of industrial change.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of industrialization’s effects on urbanization, labor, and social reform, its global influence, and connections to modern technological transformations and Saudi Arabia’s innovation goals.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 638, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756792804292-3646caa1-995c-46f9-b5a0-10f2fe876511.pptx', 'SS_Hist2_G12_U2_L1.pptx', 7159794, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756792804320-d70901d9-ae3a-4f2c-85fa-bf534172a67b.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 23:00:04', '2025-09-02 02:20:23', 12),
(176, 'U2 L2: European Colonization – Exploration and Empire', '<ul><li><p>This presentation examines the causes of European exploration, including curiosity, trade, adventure, and religion, and traces the routes of key explorers during the Renaissance.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Debate on Motivations</em> (religion vs. economics), <em>Debate on Empire Builders or Invaders</em>, and <em>Source Analysis</em> of colonial impacts.</p></li><li><p>Promotes critical reflection on European expansion, its effects on indigenous societies, and how colonization influenced nationalism and global history.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 638, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756792920753-f1c3adb0-14ed-4f63-b16d-4bfe5ffd18d4.pptx', 'SS_Hist2_G12_U2_L2.pptx', 6674486, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756792920781-592df499-384f-4b9e-ba54-96d8195b501e.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 23:02:00', '2025-09-02 02:20:23', 11),
(177, 'U2 L3: The Spread of Industrialization – A Global Wave', '<ul><li><p>This presentation explores the global spread of industrialization, focusing on North America’s industrial growth, Japan’s Meiji modernization, and industrialization in colonies.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Comparison Activity</em> analyzing political freedom, economic policies, and outcomes, and <em>Timeline Creation</em> to trace industrial growth across regions.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of how industrialization differed between independent nations and colonies, highlighting economic exploitation and global disparities.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 638, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756793053662-1c94f0cf-5ca9-4c44-8330-9274654da7e9.pptx', 'SS_Hist2_G12_U2_L3.pptx', 5145285, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756793053677-e4215b80-d1ac-4072-8a8c-5cf75ad2986c.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 23:04:13', '2025-09-02 02:20:23', 10),
(178, 'U2 L4: The Economic and Social Consequences of Industrialization', '<ul><li><p>This presentation examines the economic changes brought by industrialization, including factory working conditions, child labor, urbanization, and shifts in social structure.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Role Play</em> between workers and owners to debate problems and propose reforms, and <em>Case Study Review</em> of labor movements.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of the hardships of industrial society, the role of reforms and worker rights, and Islamic values on wealth-sharing and protection of the poor.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 638, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756793966328-07dbd34f-7580-4e4b-8979-43ed772326bc.pptx', 'SS_Hist2_G12_U2_L4.pptx', 11914636, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756793966950-53739719-b4fc-4190-a2dc-d3dbfe9d6ddc.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 23:19:26', '2025-09-02 02:20:23', 9),
(179, 'U3 L1: World War I – The Great War', '<ul><li><p>This presentation examines the long-term causes of World War I, the assassination of Archduke Ferdinand, trench warfare, new technologies, and the global impact beyond Europe.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>WWI Alliances Simulation</em> to model pre-war diplomacy and <em>Technology Role Cards</em> to explore warfare innovations.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of the human cost of the war, the Treaty of Versailles, its consequences on the Muslim world, and Islamic principles of justice in conflict resolution.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 638, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756794396796-d8307bc2-0434-4406-8683-b1be6734fc53.pptx', 'SS_Hist2_G12_U3_L1.pptx', 24750545, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756794399161-93ca2779-e42f-4d81-b346-b993b74674de.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 23:26:39', '2025-09-02 02:20:23', 8),
(182, 'U3 L3: The Cold War – Ideological Confrontation', '<ul><li><p>This presentation examines the Cold War rivalry between capitalism and communism, tracing key events such as the Iron Curtain, Truman Doctrine, Berlin Blockade, proxy wars, and the Cuban Missile Crisis.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Ideology Sorting</em> of values into capitalism or communism, and an <em>Interactive Reflection on Global Justice</em> comparing Cold War systems with Islamic principles of fairness and peace.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of how superpower competition shaped world politics, the ethical dilemmas of aid and warfare, and the collapse of the USSR in 1991.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 638, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756795842993-bf7db4c6-3a0f-4ebf-8048-335119e423cf.pptx', 'SS_Hist2_G12_U3_L3.pptx', 35877962, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756795846873-2853563c-d88c-4fbd-ac9a-4224b859aa59.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-01 23:50:46', '2025-09-02 02:21:16', 6),
(186, 'U3 L4: Regional Conflicts and Their Global Impact', '<ul><li><p>This presentation examines major regional conflicts of the late 20th century, including the Arab-Israeli conflict, the Iran-Iraq War, the Soviet-Afghan War, and the Gulf War.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Conflict Match-Up</em> to identify key features and a <em>Peace Negotiation Simulation</em> to explore strategies for conflict resolution.</p></li><li><p>Promotes awareness of the human cost of war, refugee crises, and the importance of peaceful resolution through international cooperation and justice.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 638, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756798680025-ae6535ce-bc04-499e-80ee-81f69381f7ec.pptx', 'SS_Hist2_G12_U3_L4.pptx', 38220094, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756798684223-29b73dcb-4b68-4279-a96b-25ac4e404664.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-02 00:38:04', '2025-09-02 02:21:16', 5),
(187, 'U4 L1: The Rise of Globalization', '<ul><li><p>This presentation introduces globalization, tracing its roots from the Silk Road through the Age of Exploration and the Industrial Revolution to the modern era.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Globalization Sort</em> and <em>Globalization Debate,</em> where students argue whether globalization brings more benefits or harm, using history and Islamic values as evidence.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of the drivers of globalization, its cultural and environmental impacts, and the role of Islamic civilization in shaping global connections.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 638, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756799435769-296c6e5a-7bff-40cb-abb6-ec1bf9b53e3e.pptx', 'SS_Hist2_G12_U4_L1.pptx', 36057878, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756799439675-f6cbd9da-cf5e-47d8-9392-6b5f17b293e6.png', 'draft', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-02 00:50:39', '2025-09-02 02:21:27', 4),
(188, 'U4 L2: Economic Impacts of Globalization', '<ul><li><p>This presentation explores the economic dimensions of globalization, including trade, market access, foreign direct investment, and technology.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Cause &amp; Effect Match</em> and <em>Globalization Think Tank,</em> where students design a fair global economy plan guided by Islamic principles.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of the benefits and challenges of globalization, such as income inequality, labor exploitation, and environmental costs, while drawing lessons from China, India, and Saudi Arabia’s Vision 2030.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 638, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756799530386-986c4d8b-fb4a-4470-adb1-ef517078cd1f.pptx', 'SS_Hist2_G12_U4_L2.pptx', 8831052, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756799530585-da23b393-32d3-4210-b6ba-c5f1035e3dce.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-02 00:52:10', '2025-09-02 02:20:36', 3),
(189, 'U4 L3: Cultural and Social Impacts of Globalization', '<ul><li><p>This presentation explores cultural exchange through globalization, including language, fashion, food, and media, alongside Islamic perspectives on cultural diversity.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Global Culture Map</em> and <em>Cultural Preservation Task Force,</em> where teams propose plans to protect traditions while engaging globally.</p></li><li><p>Promotes awareness of the risks of cultural homogenization, support for indigenous voices, the role of digital media in empowerment, and the importance of cultural solidarity.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 638, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756799625126-4b88da49-e0ad-4fac-ae8b-2cb5593d9020.pptx', 'SS_Hist2_G12_U4_L3.pptx', 18041102, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756799626575-721ed6f3-7e45-4933-9a83-8daeda1ba16f.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-02 00:53:46', '2025-09-02 02:29:16', 2),
(190, 'U4 L4: Global Issues and International Cooperation', '<ul><li><p>This presentation examines key global issues such as climate change, pandemics, and international security, highlighting the importance of cooperation through global agreements and organizations.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Global Crisis Simulation</em> and <em>Match the Organization to the Role</em> exercise, along with case studies on COVID-19 and the Paris Agreement.</p></li><li><p>Promotes awareness of shared global responsibilities, Islamic principles of environmental stewardship, and the value of collaboration in building peace and resilience.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 638, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756799698755-5ae6407f-491c-41df-8f32-e3d173e40d6a.pptx', 'SS_Hist2_G12_U4_L4.pptx', 8552836, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756799698911-0a2ba66d-ed9c-4b4d-9e6f-d40e0c16121e.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-02 00:54:58', '2025-09-02 02:29:16', 1),
(192, 'U3 L2: World War II – Global Conflict', '<ul><li><p>This presentation explores the causes and course of World War II, from the Treaty of Versailles and economic collapse to the rise of Hitler, Axis aggression, and major turning points such as Stalingrad and D-Day.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: <em>Timeline Assembly</em>, <em>Battle Analysis Challenge</em>, and <em>Debate: Just or Unjust Peace?</em> comparing Versailles with Islamic principles of justice.</p></li><li><p>Promotes understanding of WWII’s devastation, the importance of fair peace settlements, and the value of resolving conflicts through reason and compassion in line with Islamic teachings.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 436, 638, 1, 'backend/uploads/1756803885269-cd2de620-a27a-4af3-882e-21137cf4dfd4.pptx', 'SS_Hist2_G12_U3_L2.pptx', 19854183, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1756803886972-e171254a-1158-4346-a1ec-7c62f7ca7499.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-02 02:04:47', '2025-09-02 02:21:04', 7),
(193, 'Sample Resource', '<ul><li><p>This presentation on <strong>Sharing and Helping Others</strong> introduces students to the meaning of sharing, the concept of Zakat, and everyday ways to help others.</p></li><li><p>Includes interactive activities: Sharing Circle Time, One Good Deed a Day calendar, and a story on the Prophet’s (PBUH) kindness.</p></li><li><p>Promotes kindness, charity, and Islamic values of helping and caring for others.</p></li></ul><p></p>', 366, 434, 627, 1, 'backend/uploads/1759241707412-d78c075d-e427-4a74-bae9-7a8537340225.pptx', 'Presentation1.pptx', 3853207, 'pptx', 'backend/uploads/1759241757954-49e2b38d-172a-4cac-b36a-aa2e3ee7c2b7.png', 'draft', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2025-09-30 07:15:07', '2025-09-30 07:15:57', 0);
